    By default, a :class:`Gio.DBusServer` or server-side :class:`Gio.DBusConnection` will allow
    any authentication mechanism to be used. If you only want to allow D-Bus
    connections with the ``EXTERNAL`` mechanism, which makes use of credentials
    passing and is the recommended mechanism for modern Unix platforms such
    as Linux and the BSD family, you would use a signal handler like this:

    .. code-block:: c

        static gboolean
        on_allow_mechanism (:class:`Gio.DBusAuthObserver` *observer,
                            const gchar       *mechanism,
                            gpointer           user_data)
        {
          if (g_strcmp0 (mechanism, "EXTERNAL") == 0)
            {
              return TRUE;
            }

          return FALSE;
        }

    ## Controlling Authorization

    By default, a :class:`Gio.DBusServer` or server-side :class:`Gio.DBusConnection` will accept
    connections from any successfully authenticated user (but not from
    anonymous connections using the ``ANONYMOUS`` mechanism). If you only
    want to allow D-Bus connections from processes owned by the same uid
    as the server, since GLib 2.68, you should use the
    ``G_DBUS_SERVER_FLAGS_AUTHENTICATION_REQUIRE_SAME_USER`` flag. ItŌĆÖs equivalent
    to the following signal handler:

    .. code-block:: c

        static gboolean
        on_authorize_authenticated_peer (:class:`Gio.DBusAuthObserver` *observer,
                                         :class:`Gio.IOStream`         *stream,
                                         :class:`Gio.Credentials`      *credentials,
                                         gpointer           user_data)
        {
          gboolean authorized;

          authorized = FALSE;
          if (credentials != NULL)
            {
              :class:`Gio.Credentials` *own_credentials;
              own_credentials = :meth:`Gio.Credentials.new`;
              if (:meth:`Gio.Credentials.is_same_user` (credentials, own_credentials, NULL))
                authorized = TRUE;
              g_object_unref (own_credentials);
            }

          return authorized;
        }
    """
